Texts.Chs: 一幅最令人不安的画，让人想起科技发展部潜在的信息。
Texts.Eng: A most disturbing painting that is reminiscent of Miniknog subliminal messaging.

Texts.Chs: 一幅奇特的人物肖像画。
Texts.Eng: A strangely done portrait of a human being.

Texts.Chs: 另一幅抽象画，据说是人类的起源。
Texts.Eng: Another abstract painting, reputedly of Human provenance.

Texts.Chs: 人类艺术作品永远不可能达到我们猫族所能达到的精致水平。
Texts.Eng: Human artwork can never reach the same level of refinement as what we Felins can do.

Texts.Chs: 我不懂艺术。我希望用更多的暴力来代替。
Texts.Eng: I do not understand art. I wish to do more violence instead.

Texts.Chs: 我想这种想法会要了你的命，尤其是当你想到这件艺术品的时候。
Texts.Eng: I guess that thoughts can kill you, especially if you think about this artwork.

Texts.Chs: 我听说人类对艺术的天赋是不可预测的，然而在地球毁灭后幸存下来的只是它的残渣。
Texts.Eng: I've heard that Human flair for the arts can be unpredictable, and what survived the destruction of Earth has been its dregs.
Information wants to be free all the time.

Texts.Chs: 这让人想起了原力使用者使用的思维技巧。
Texts.Eng: It's reminiscent of Mind Tricks used by Force users.

Texts.Chs: 这既美妙又恐怖。就像一家养老院。
Texts.Eng: This is both wonderful and horrifying. Like a retirement home.

Texts.Chs: 奇怪的是，这令人不安。几乎不可能把视线集中在图像上。
Texts.Eng: This is oddly disturbing. It is impossible to focus on the image.

Texts.Chs: 这让我想起了Ithraax Var那冰冷的沙漠。
Texts.Eng: This reminds me of the cold deserts of Ithraax Var.

Texts.Chs: 这幅奇怪的画名为“思想的萌芽”。我会被震住，不知道自己是怎么想的。
Texts.Eng: This strange painting is titled ''Germ of an Idea''. I'll be stumped as to what I think about this.

Texts.Chs: 什么？眼睛不要注视它。伤害大脑。烧掉吧！
Texts.Eng: WHAT? Eyes not focus on. Hurts brain. Burn!

Texts.Chs: 为什么这个可怜的黄色家伙被其他黄色物体刺穿了？这是不对的。
Texts.Eng: Why is this poor yellow dude impaled by some other yellow object? now that's not right.

Texts.Chs: 为什么还还还要在这里作画？愚愚愚蠢。
Texts.Eng: Why iss painting even here? Sstupid.
